<title>USA: Beverly Pa. workers ratify 4-year contract.</title>
<headline>Beverly Pa. workers ratify 4-year contract.</headline>
<dateline>HARRISBURG, Pa. 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>The union representing employees at 19 nursing homes of Beverly Enterprises Inc in Pennsylvania said Monday the workers had ratified a new four-year contract.</p>
<p>The Service Employees International Union said the employees received wage increases of 3.0 to 5.0 percent annually, raising the average wage to more than $9 an nour by the end of the contract.</p>
<p>Beverly agreed to extend dental and vision benefits to part-time as well as full-time workers, it said.</p>
<p>The healthcare company also agreed to common expiration dates for all work contracts, it said.</p>
<p>The new contract replaces one that expired November 30, 1995, it said.</p>
